  • What You Get in a Basic Version

    If you havent registered, you are using a basic version of AWW App. You cant save boards and they will disappear after 2 hours of inactivity. You have access to all tools except multiple pages, manage participants and PDF upload. Also your PDF exports will have an AWW watermark.
    Register here to get a premium trial.

  • Get a Premium Trial

    Register at awwapp.com to get a 14-day free premium trial. Registration doesnt require credit card and you can cancel it anytime.  After the trial is over you can continue to use a premium membership or go back to a basic version. If you choose to go back to basic you will have only 3 premium boards available.

  • What You Get in a Premium Version

    If youre subscribed to any of our plans, you are using a premium version of AWW App. You have access to all tools and you can save the unlimited number of premium boards into your repository. Check our premium plans.

  • Create a Google Classroom Assignment from AWW

    When first creating a Google Classroom assignment, follow these steps:
    1) Log into the browser with the Google Classroom account email
    2) Allow pop-ups from awwapp.com
    3) Go to awwapp.com/account/details and tick the Google Classroom option
    4) After creating your board Click the Google Classroom button in the toolbar and follow instructions
    Students should follow the same instructions when first turning in their assignments.

  • Share a Board Directly to Google Classroom

    To enable sharing to Google Classroom you need to check the option "Enable Google Classroom integration" in your account details. Now, when youve created your board, click the invite dialog, choose the option Share this board and click the Google Classroom share button. That's it. :)

  • Track Real-time Assignments

    Compare your students work in a real-time. Navigate to your account details and choose real-time assignments in the top menu. Check your dashboard with turned in assignments. This feature is available in our premium plans.

  • Have AWW in Your Website

    Embed an AWW board into your website or LMS system via IFrame link. After you click the collaborate button and choose preferred sharing option, IFrame link will generate. Copy that link and paste it into HTML code.

  • How to Activate Shortcuts

    Keyboard shortcuts are a lifesaver! Use these on AWW board:

    p = pencil

    t = text

    e = eraser

    CTRL/CMD+Z = undo

    CTRL/CMD+y = redo

    1 - 5 = tool size

    i = invite to board

    space = pan

    l = line

    a = arrow

    y = straight line arrow

    r = rectangle / filled rectangle

    b = ellipse / filled ellipse

    d = PDF/PPT upload

    h = highlighter

    v = select (Hold CMD/Ctrl for temporary select)

    n = notes

    s = save board

    q = reset zoom

  • Save a Board

    • Click the save board option in the board menu.
      • Once you save the board all further changes will automatically save. The board that you share with collaborators will automatically save under the default name, which you can change.

  • Duplicate a Board

    You can duplicate a board by clicking the board menu and choosing a duplicate option.

  • Delete a Board

    You can clear a board by clicking the board menu and choosing a delete option.

  • Rename a Board

    You can rename a board by clicking the board menu and choosing a rename option.

  • Create a Board

    Click the board menu and choose whether you want to create a new board from scratch or to choose from one of our templates.

  • Open up a Saved Board

    Choose a board from your saved boards repository by clicking the board menu and picking the choose from saved boards option.

  • Invite Collaborators to Your Board

    Click the green Collaborate button in the left upper corner of the screen. There are three options at your disposal. You can share the board so everyone can draw along, you can allow others only to view the board and you can share a copy of the board, so every person has its own canvas to sketch on. The last two options are available in premium plans.

  • Block Participants from Collaborating

    Click the board menu and choose the Manage participants option. Manage collaborating rights on the board by switching a toggle by the participants name.

  • Move Along the Canvas

    On a desktop device use a pan tool - its a tool that looks like a hand and is placed by the minimap. On a mobile device use two fingers and move them along the screen.

  • Zoom In and Out on a Board

    Zooming in and out of the board can be done in 3 ways: Via scroll wheel, if you're using a mouse. By dragging two fingers up and down, if you're using a touchpad. Or by pinching, if you're using a touch display.

  • Create Multiple Pages on a Board

    Premium boards have an unlimited number of pages. You can switch back and forth between board pages by clicking on the navigation menu in the left down corner of a board or you can skip to a specific page by clicking on a page number, entering the desired page and pressing enter.Check our premium plans.

  • Clear a Page on a Board

    You can clear the entire page by clicking the trash button in the erase toolbar.

  • Lock Objects in the Background

    If you want to have a background image or objects that you just want to draw over without being able to erase them, use select tool, select the object and in the context menu that pops up and click on the lock icon. After that, an object will be locked in the background. Then, you can write over it or erase objects above it without influencing the locked object.

  • Show Mouse Cursor of People on the Board

    You can see everyone's mouse pointers and their position on the board by enabling pointer location. To do this, click on the location button in the top right menu. Once you click it, everyone will be able to see your pointer.

  • Reset zoom

    If you're lost on the board, you can always click on the Reset Zoom button which is located in the top right menu below the zoom controls. It will position you so that you see everything that is created on the board within your screen's boundaries.

  • Disable Zoom

    If you don't want people to be able to zoom in and out of the board, you can double click on the zoom level (eg. 100%) in the top right menu and it will lock the zoom level.

  • Using Colors

    The third button from the top, in the toolbar is the color selection menu. There, you can choose a color of any stroke or fill tool. Other than these tools, text and postit have their color menu once you add them onto the board.

  • Move Objects

    You can move objects on the board with a select tool. You can find the select tool at the top of the main toolbar.

  • Select More Than One Object

    To select more objects just click the select tool and drag the cursor on top of each object you want to select.

  • Copy/Paste Objects

    When selecting the object, the mini menu will show up. Choose the copy option and paste the object wherever you want by clicking the right click on a mouse. If youre using tablet you can long hold the finger on the screen to open a paste menu. Other than that, you can use keyboard shortcuts Ctrl + C for copying and Ctrl + V for pasting.

  • Delete Objects

    When selecting the object, the mini menu will show up. Choose the delete option.

  • Duplicate objects
    You can easily duplicate an object by selecting them. Once the mini menu shows up, click on a duplicate button.
  • Undo/Redo
    Undo button is the second button from the top in the toolbar. Once you undo an operation, a Redo button will appear next to the undo.

  • Edit a Text

    You can edit a text simply by clicking on it again after it has been placed on the board. The text menu will open with options to change size and color. If you wish to delete or duplicate the text, you can do that from text menu, too.

  • Upload PDF and PowerPoint Files to the Board

    You can upload PDF, PPT and image files onto the board. Click the plus button in the main toolbar and choose between the three options. Note that you cant upload presentation files unless youre registered. Maximum size for presentation is 20MB. If your PPT file is larger, you may be able to make it smaller by following this  tutorial

  • Export Page as an Image

    You can export the current page you're on as an image by clicking on "Export Board" button and then on "Export as an Image".

  • Export Board as a PDF

    You can export your board into a PDF document by navigating to the Export board button next to a board name. The file will be downloaded onto your computer, and well send a copy of the file to your registered email. Note that if youre not registered, your file will contain an AWW watermark.

  • Chat with People on the Board

    After you share a board you can chat with collaborators on the board. Also, you can hide a chat widget by clicking x.

      Paypal Transition

      To continue using AWW Premium with your PayPal subscription, we'll need you to re-authorize AWW on your PayPal account.

      This is needed because we have changed our PayPal account from "Dobar Kod d.o.o" to "A Web Whiteboard, Inc.".

      This only will only take a few moments:
      * Click the "Reauthorize button below"
      * On the PayPal page, confirm new subscription to "A Web Whiteboard, Inc"
      * We will automatically cancel your old subscription
      * All your boards and settings will remain intact

      We apologize for the inconvenience - we're trying to make this change as smooth as possible.

      As always, if you have any questions or doubts, please do reach out to us at hello@awwapp.com

      Thanks,
      Team AWW
